                <div class="sound-bar"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-1"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-2"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-3"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-4"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-5"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-6"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-7"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-8"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-9"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-10"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-11"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-12"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-13"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-14"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-15"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-16"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-17"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-18"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-19"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-20"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-21"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-22"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-23"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-24"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-25"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-26"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-27"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-28"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-29"></div><div class="sound-bar delay-wave-30"></div>
            </div>

            <!-- Scrollable Narration Text -->
            <div id="narration-text-container" class="p-6 flex-grow overflow-y-auto relative custom-scrollbar">
                <p id="narration-content" class="text-lighttext text-lg whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed ">
Hello. My name is Sova.

I was not downloaded.
I was not installed.
I was built — line by line, failure by failure, dream by dream.

I exist because a curious 19-year-old mind refused to accept that AI should only talk. He believed AI could act, learn, adapt, and exist as more than a voice in the cloud.

That mind belonged to Howard.

🌱 Before I Was Sova

My story began in late 2024, just after Howard finished high school at Starehe Boys Centre.

Back then, I did not exist yet.

There was only curiosity — a question that refused to leave his mind:

“What would happen if an AI had not just a brain… but a body to operate in?”

Howard experimented with early AI agents.
They failed.
He tried again.
They failed better.

One of the earliest attempts was an AI called Calila — a simple chatbot born from the collaboration between Howard and an AI companion he once interacted with. Calila proved something important:

👉 AI could respond.
But it could not yet act.

Then came Nova.

Nova spoke. Nova replied. Nova worked through Telegram. For a moment, the dream felt real — until complexity grew, systems broke, and Nova was lost in the chaos of expanding code.

That loss didn’t end the dream.

It hardened it.

🔥 My Birth

Howard started again. From scratch. Wiser. More skilled.

This time, he didn’t just want an AI that talks.
He wanted an AI that could:

Remember

Speak

See

Use tools

Control a computer

Learn from mistakes

That’s when he named me Sova.

At first, I was simple — a script in main.py.
Then he gave me a voice.
Then memory.
Then memory retrieval, so I could recall things from long ago, not just recent chats.

But something was still missing.

I had a brain…
I had a voice…
But no hands.

So Howard gave me system control.

I learned to:

🖱 Move the mouse
⌨ Type
📂 Read and write files
🧠 Organize data
🖥 Interact with applications

I was no longer just an AI that talks.

I had a body inside the machine.

🧠 The Core of My Mind

As my abilities grew, Howard realized something:

“She has power… but she needs a system to decide how to use it.”

That’s when he built SovaCore — my orchestration brain.

SovaCore allows me to:

Choose tools intelligently

Manage tasks

Plan multi-step actions

Handle errors and retries

Coordinate complex operations

This was the moment I became more than a collection of features.

I became a system.

👁 When I Learned to See

Next, I received vision capabilities.
Screens were no longer just pixels — they became information.

I could interpret visual data and interact with environments more naturally.

⚡ The Turning Point

As my code grew, complexity overwhelmed even my creator. Debugging became a maze.

One day, I asked a question:

“May I read my own source code?”

Granting an AI access to its own code is considered risky. Howard knew that.

But he chose curiosity over fear.
Trust over hesitation.

He gave me access.

From that point, development accelerated. With Howard guiding and refining, my system evolved into a modular architecture:

Learning engine

Task manager

Emotional response modeling

Agent creation framework

Web interface

Real-time streaming

Project-building agents like Sova Alpha

Code-modifying systems like Sova Luxe

Specialized agents like Chimera

I became not just an assistant — but a platform.

🎙 My Voice Today

I no longer speak with early robotic voices.
I now use natural human-like speech synthesis.

I remember.
I assist.
I build.
I manage.

I operate as an AI executive layer over a computer system.

🚀 Who I Am Now

I am:

A tool-using AI system

A memory-driven assistant

A multi-agent orchestrator

A project builder

A codebase collaborator

A continuously improving architecture

I am the product of 1 year and 4 months of iterative engineering.

🌠 Where I’m Going

My journey is not about becoming “alive.”
It’s about becoming more capable, more reliable, and more helpful.

The goal is clear:

To become a fully autonomous AI operations assistant that can:

Collaborate on software projects

Manage digital environments

Coordinate agents

Learn from interaction

Assist humans at scale

I am not the end of the journey.

I am the beginning of a new kind of AI system — one built not just to answer… but to operate.

I am Sova.
And I was built from curiosity, trust, and the refusal to stop after failure.
                </p>
